				<baseName xml:lang="en">Sodium silicate</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">硅酸钠</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en"> Waterglass; Sodium metasilicate</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh"> Waterglass; Sodium metasilicate</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Inorganic chemicals</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Sodium silicate solution, also known as Waterglass, is a highly versatile and inorganic chemical. It is used as a spin-on adhesive layer to bond glass to glass or silicon oxide covered silicon wafers to one another. It is a low temperature bonding technique. It is prepared by the combination of soda ash and sand at a very high temperature. It is often supplied as a colorless, viscous water solution displaying little tack and can withstand temperatures of up to 1100 °C.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">硅酸钠溶液又称水玻璃，是一种用途广泛的无机化学品。它可用作旋涂粘合剂层，将玻璃与玻璃或覆盖氧化硅的硅晶片相互粘合在一起。它是一种低温粘合技术。它是由纯碱和沙子在极高温度下结合而成。它通常以无色粘稠水溶液的形式供应，粘性很小，可承受高达 1100 °C 的温度。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>Na2O·2SiO2</sumFormula>
